
Plasma growth hormone, zzso insulin and cortisol response to oral administration of L-dopa and in zzso test were investigated in 18 obese zzso The results were compared with the results obtained in 10 normal zzso The obese subjects displayed a lack of growth hormone responsiveness to L-dopa and a diminished zzso responsiveness to zzso There was no significant difference in zzso response to zzso in normal and obese zzso zzso subjects showed normal increments of plasma cortisol following induction of zzso although there was no consistent cortisol response after L-dopa zzso A blood zzso response following L-dopa administration was seen in most of normal subjects while no zzso of blood zzso was noticed in obese zzso 

